  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/pull/6042",
  "title": "feat(ui-components): migrate `Hits` component",
  "body": "This PR introduces `createHits()`, available from `instantsearch-ui-components`. This method can be used by the Hits widget from each flavor to setup a UI component that renders appropriately.\r\n\r\n## Design considerations\r\n\r\nThe UI component expects from widgets the following props:\r\n\r\n```tsx\r\nexport type HitsProps<THit> = React.ComponentProps<'div'> & {\r\n  hits: THit[];\r\n  itemComponent: (props: {\r\n    hit: THit;\r\n    index: number;\r\n    className: string;\r\n    onClick: () => void;\r\n    onAuxClick: () => void;\r\n  }) => JSX.Element;\r\n  sendEvent: SendEventForHits;\r\n  classNames?: Partial<HitsClassNames>;\r\n  emptyComponent?: (props: { className: string }) => JSX.Element;\r\n};\r\n```\r\n\r\n**`itemComponent`**\r\n\r\nUsed by the component as a direct child of an `<ol>`. Widgets use this to wrap the item template / hit component / item slot.\r\n\r\n**`classNames`**\r\n\r\nThe class list is from IS.js/RISH. Vue's component maps its specific structure to the more common one.\r\n\r\n**`emptyComponent`**\r\n\r\nWhen provided, the component renders this instead of returning an empty list if there are no hits. Only IS.js has this currently.\r\n\r\n\r\nFX-2729",
